author: Teleplay by Aaron Sorkin
---
context: spoken by Josiah Bartlett
---
location: "The West Wing", Season 3 Episode 5: "War Crimes"
---
text: Words! Words, when spoken out loud for the sake of performance are music. They have rhythm and pitch and timbre and volume. These are the properties of music, and music has the ability to find us and move us and lift us up in ways that literal meaning can't.
